The 2019 MyBroadband Conference and Expo will take place on Thursday 17 October at the Gallagher Convention Centre and is the one event which every ICT executive should attend. The annual MyBroadband Conference is the premier ICT event in South Africa and the meeting place for the country’s IT and telecoms community. Delegates will hear from top speakers, including MTN SA CEO Godfrey Motsa, Liquid Telecom CEO Reshaad Sha, and former Telkom COO Prof. Brian Armstrong. Other speakers include Vodacom chief officer Jorge Mendes, SqwidNet MD Phathizwe Malinga, and Q-KON Africa CEO Dawie de Wet. There will also be a panel discussion chaired by Jan Vermeulen, who will be joined by Supersonic MD Calvin Collett, Vodacom executive Jannie van Zyl, and Huawei SA CTO Akhram Mohamed. Delegates will also get the opportunity to interact with South Africa’s top telecommunications and IT companies and enjoy special deals from the conference exhibitors. This year there are over 50 conference exhibitors and partners, which include MTN as the lead sponsor, Liquid Telecom SA as the co-lead sponsor, and Vodacom as the title sponsor. Other prominent exhibitors include Sqwidnet, Huawei, Q-Kon Africa, Mind The Speed, WIOCC, and Africa Data Centres. People who want to register for the 2019 MyBroadband Conference and Expo are encouraged to do so soon. The tickets cover all aspects of the event, including access to the expo and conference, lunch, and refreshments.